# Accessibility

The site supports artists with disabilities. Every PR with UI must pass axe-core in CI and a manual screen-reader check on the changed routes.

- **Semantic HTML first.** `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation. No `<div onClick>`.
- **One `<h1>` per page.** Heading levels descend without skipping.
- **All images need alt text.** Decorative images use `alt=""`. Keystatic enforces this in the schema for artist headshots.
- **Color contrast ≥ 4.5:1** for body text, ≥ 3:1 for large text. Verified in Storybook-equivalent `/dev/playground`.
- **Keyboard reachable.** Every interactive element has a visible focus ring. Use `:focus-visible` not `:focus`.
- **Forms have labels.** Every `<input>` has an associated `<label>` (not placeholder-as-label).
- **Live regions** for form submission feedback (`aria-live="polite"`).
- **Reduced motion.** Wrap animations in `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`.
- **Accessibility statement** at `/accessibility` is required by NY law for public-facing nonprofit sites; do not delete it.
